@startuml Render_Deployment_Architecture
title Detailed Deployment View: Cloud (Render)

skinparam componentStyle uml2
skinparam node {
    BackgroundColor White
    BorderColor black
}

actor "User (Browser)" as User

node "GitHub" <<Version Control>> as GH {
    artifact "Main Branch (Codebase)" as Repo
}

package "Render Cloud Platform" {
    node "Static Site Service" <<Service>> as FrontendNode {
        component "React v19 SPA" #AliceBlue {
            [Axios Client]
            [PDF Report Generator (jsPDF)]
            [Assessment State (Context API)]
        }
    }

    node "Web Service" <<Service>> as BackendNode {
        component "FastAPI Server" #PaleGreen {
            [API (main.py, models.py)]
            [Ingestion (Chromadb)]
            [Orchestrator (pipeline.py)]
        }
        
        node "Multi-Agent Pipeline" #GhostWhite {
            component "Alignment Agent" as Agent1
            component "Gap Agent" as Agent2
            component "Synthesis Agent" as Agent3
        }
        
        database "Ephemeral Disk Store" <<Wiped on Deploy>> as Storage {
            folder "uploaded_files/"
            folder "chroma_db/"
            folder "assessment_history/"
        }
    }
}

node "LLM Providers (External)" as APIs {
    component "OpenAI (gpt-5-nano)" as OpenAI
    component "Anthropic (Claude 4.6)" as Anthropic
    component "Google (Gemini 3)" as Google
    component "Ollama (Local/RPC)" as Ollama
}

' Interactions
Repo -down-> FrontendNode : Build & Deploy (npm)
Repo -down-> BackendNode : Build & Deploy (pip)

User -down-> FrontendNode : HTTPS (port 443)
[Axios Client] -right-> [API (main.py, models.py)] : REST/JSON (VITE_API_URL)

[Orchestrator (pipeline.py)] -down-> [Ingestion (Chromadb)] : Retrieve Context
[Orchestrator (pipeline.py)] -down-> Agent1 : Step 1: Align
[Orchestrator (pipeline.py)] -down-> Agent2 : Step 2: Gap
[Orchestrator (pipeline.py)] -down-> Agent3 : Step 3: Synthesis

Agent1 -right-> APIs : API Requests
Agent2 -right-> APIs : API Requests
Agent3 -right-> APIs : API Requests

[API (main.py, models.py)] -down-> Storage : File I/O & DB Persistence

note bottom of Storage
  **Critical Limitation**:
  In Render's free tier, this disk is NOT persistent.
  Data is lost during restarts/redeployments.
end note

@enduml
